The [libbson.rc.in|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/3e942aa8ea0e7f7563ba8925ef1479e47006197e/src/libbson/libbson.rc.in#L4] file unnecessarily (re)defines {{BSON_COMPILATION}} which is [already set via target properties|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/3e942aa8ea0e7f7563ba8925ef1479e47006197e/src/libbson/CMakeLists.txt#L219], producing the following warning when compiled:

{code:none}
warning RC4005: 'BSON_COMPILATION' : redefinition
{code}

The [libmongoc.rc.in|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/3e942aa8ea0e7f7563ba8925ef1479e47006197e/src/libmongoc/libmongoc.rc.in#L4] file does not have this problem.

h1. Summary

An assertion fails when creating a legacy exhaust cursor receiving empty results:

{code}
src/libbson/src/bson/bson-reader.c:526 bson_reader_new_from_data(): precondition failed: data
{code}

This applies when creating an exhaust cursor with the legacy op code OP_QUERY. The C driver uses OP_QUERY for exhaust cursor when [connected to mongod < 4.2|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/0e771ca6b16098a82cb05346622c712906253faf/src/libmongoc/tests/test-mongoc-exhaust.c#L35].

This appears to be a regression introduced in 1.24.0 as part of CDRIVER-4617.

h1. Additional Information

Here is a regression test:
{code:c}
static void
test_exhaust_cursor_no_match (void *context)
{
   BSON_UNUSED (context);
   bson_error_t error;
   mongoc_client_t *client = test_framework_new_default_client ();
   mongoc_collection_t *coll = mongoc_client_get_collection (client, "db", "coll");

   // Drop collection to remove prior test data.
   mongoc_collection_drop (coll, NULL /* ignore error */);

   mongoc_cursor_t *cursor = mongoc_collection_find_with_opts (
      coll, tmp_bson ("{}"), tmp_bson ("{'exhaust': true }"), NULL /* read_prefs */);
   const bson_t *result;
   while (mongoc_cursor_next (cursor, &result)); // Assertion failure!

   mongoc_cursor_destroy (cursor);
   mongoc_collection_destroy (coll);
   mongoc_client_destroy (client);
}

{code}

